MTN has launched its Wowza Wednesday promotion, offering new post-paid clients 50GB of data and 10,000 MTN-to-MTN minutes per month for 24 months. According to the MTN blog, this will see customers who sign up for select tariff plans with an LTE device receive 1,200GB of data and 240,000 minutes over two years. The deal is available today, 21 December 2016. “The 30GB once-off data bundles will still be provisioned in the first month to customers who sign up on a long-term contract with an LTE device,” said MTN. The contracts which form part of the deal are: